{{Quote|I am capable of speaking Basic if that is how we must proceed.''"<br />"''That will not be necessary. Use your native language. I have brought my own translating droid.|A Mairan ambassador and Tenel Ka|<ref name="Lightsabers" />}}
The [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Mairan/Legends|Mairan]] [[Species/Legends|species]] of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Maires/Legends|Maires]] spoke a '''language''' composed of [[Music/Legends|music]]-like notes played on a [[shell flute]].<ref name="Lightsabers" /> In [[23 ABY/Legends|23 ABY]],<ref name="TERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of ''[[Young Jedi Knights: Lightsabers]]'' to [[23 ABY/Legends|23 ABY]].</ref> [[Tenel Ka Djo|Tenel Ka]], the [[Hapan]]-[[Dathomir/Legends|Dathomiri]] [[Prince/Legends|princess]], used the [[Translator droid/Legends|translator droid]] [[M-TD]] to talk with a [[Unidentified Mairan ambassador|Mairan ambassador]] who was using a shell [[Flute/Legends|flute]] to speak his native [[Language/Legends|language]].<ref name="Lightsabers" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Mairan language first appeared in the [[1998]] ''[[Young Jedi Knights: Lightsabers]]'', a young reader's novel by [[Kevin J. Anderson]] and [[Rebecca Moesta]].<ref name="Lightsabers" />

